<subSubSection pageId="835" pageNumber="836" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="835" pageNumber="836">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName LSID="946AD65E-B766-5715-A1AF-D88F7518B259" authority="Bonelli, 1810" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Nemotarsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="835" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Zuphiini">Zuphiini Bonelli, 1810</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="835" pageNumber="836" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="835" pageNumber="836">
<taxonomicName genus="Zuphietae" lsidName="" pageId="835" pageNumber="836" rank="genus">Zuphietae</taxonomicName>
Bonelli, 1810: Tabula Synoptica. Type genus: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1805" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Zuphium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="835" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="835" pageNumber="836">Zuphium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille, 1805.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="835" pageNumber="836" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="835" pageNumber="836">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="835" pageNumber="836">
Worldwide, with about 290 species (Lorenz 2005: 504-507, excluding 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jedlicka" authorityYear="1941" genus="Planetina" lsidName="" pageId="835" pageNumber="836" rank="genus">Planetina</taxonomicName>
) arrayed in 20 genera. The tribe is represented in the Northern Hemisphere by about 65 species (22% of the world fauna). Three subtribes are recognized: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Basilewsky" authorityYear="1951" genus="Leleupidiina" lsidName="" pageId="835" pageNumber="836" rank="genus">Leleupidiina</taxonomicName>
(about 90 species in the Old World and the Australian Region), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" genus="Zuphiina" lsidName="" pageId="835" pageNumber="836" rank="genus">Zuphiina</taxonomicName>
(about 200 species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="1992" genus="Dicrodontina" lsidName="" pageId="835" pageNumber="836" rank="genus">Dicrodontina</taxonomicName>
(three species endemic to the Canary Islands).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="835" pageNumber="836" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph pageId="835" pageNumber="836">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="835" pageNumber="836">The planetines are included in this tribe by Lorenz (2005: 507). However Basilewsky (1963b), Reichardt (1967), Ball (1985), and Baehr (1986) presented arguments suggesting that planetines are probably more closely related to galeritines than to zuphiines.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
